cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) as mobile infrastructure in cellular networks, which involves wireless communication and control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of simulations to demonstrate the performance impact of incorporating different battery charging options, which suggests that it may fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of battery lifetime, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
